<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 08 at 4:26AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...PATCHY DENSE FOG THIS MORNING...
Patchy dense fog continues to impact portions of the Greater
Capital Region, Saratoga Region, the Taconics and mid Hudson
Valley of eastern New York, and western New England. Some melting
of the snow and ice pack with light precipitation has allowed for
the fog to develop. Visibilities will occasionally lower a half
mile or less. Use caution if out on the roads early this morning
by keeping a safe driving distance from other vehicles with low
beam head lights on. The fog should begin to lift after 7 am.</description>
